{"cursor":"3186","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n'Continue' is a common term in video games for the option to continue the game\nafter all of the player's lives have been lost, rather than ending the game\nand restarting from the very beginning. There may or may not be a penalty for\ndoing this, such as losing a certain number of points or being unable to\naccess bonus stages.\n","linknr":118,"url":"Continue_(video_gaming)","recorded":1362562646,"links":20,"instances":["video_gaming"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Video game gameplay","Video game terminology"],"headings":["Arcade games","See also","References","Further reading"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/A7xpg-continue.png/220px-A7xpg-continue.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/be/Gamepad.svg/30px-Gamepad.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["checkpoint","video_gaming"]],"members":["checkpoint"],"related":["Video_game","1-up","Game_over","Conspicuous_consumption","Checkpoint_(video_gaming)"]}